Author: hypocalese#3688
Content:
@ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢  Ever seen these errors when adding additional nodes to an Assetclass coin?  Misbehaving: 142.11.199.63:22165 (100 -> 101) BAN THRESHOLD EXCEEDED
 ERROR: ProcessNewBlock: CheckBlock FAILED

Author: ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢#7004
Content:
@hypocalese Yes, that means that the peer has attempted to send you a new block and the ruleset in your node believes it to be invalid
after so many times of trying to send you the same bad block, your node will ban that peer so that they don't flood you with continuous bad info

Author: hypocalese#3688
Content: @ComputerGenie üë¥üèºüì¢   That is a good explanation.  In my case I'm adding a third node and its starting with a fresh install.The third node is generating those errors.  I had a character in the wrong place in my startup script.  All set now.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: the underlying daemon is `marketmaker` daemon

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: what you build on top of it's API and name it, doesn't matter.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: BarterDEX and HyperDEX uses the exact same `marketmaker` daemon service the exact same API.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: BarterDEX is reference for developers mainly.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: and HyperDEX is end user product.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: a much polished and much better user experience designed application.

Author: Vivek#4733
Content: Can you give me the download link to HyperDex

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: please head over to #dex-hyperdex I don't have the links handy.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: or someone from support can help with hyperdex links.

Author: Vivek#4733
Content: ok. Thanks

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: no problem

Author: Vivek#4733
Content: I have a wierd question

Author: Vivek#4733
Content: I want to sell a token on a decentralized exchnage but since this token is not popular, there are no buyers for this

Author: Vivek#4733
Content: Can i sell this token on a decentraliuzed exchange

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: change the word decentralized with centralized in your question.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: the answer is no.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: it's market. if there is not buyer, you can't sell.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: where there are buyers there'll be sellers. and where there will be sellers, there will be buyers.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: on start the small exchanges get less of these. they evolve by time.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: for decentralised exchange to get such liquidity, they have to reach the point where it's convenient and fulfils the needs of those demanding customers who value their chickens. and I see HyperDEX heading towards that rapidly in user experience terms.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: we are waiting for version 2 of marketmaker. which is already in progress. hoping if it reaches to market by 2019 sometime HyperDEX will be the best in the market, and will cover what is needed for driving more liquidity attracting more buyers/sellers.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: `marketmaker` is the engine underneath. `BarterDEX` and `HyperDEX` are just the bodies.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: the HyperDEX body is beautiful and ready. it just needs more improved, better, faster engine. `marketmaker` version 2.

Author: Vivek#4733
Content: ok. Thanks for your detailed answer, you mean I cannot sell it in both either centralized or Decentralized, if there are no buyers...correct? yes, I will try HyperDex today

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: yes. market needs both buyers and sellers to do buy and sell.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: no matter where it is.

Author: Vivek#4733
Content: oh..ok. I got it. Thanks. you are awesome.

Author: grewalsatinder#9653
Content: np
